"{\"uid\": \"lewrockwell.com-2024-08-no_author-america-2-0-goes-to-the-satanic-olympics\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"August 5, 2024  I used to enjoy watching the Olympics.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 54, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"When I was still young and naive, I actually rooted for Americans in all events.\", \"from\": 55, \"to\": 135, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I loved the diving in particular, and the female gymnastics was fun to watch as well.\", \"from\": 136, \"to\": 221, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"America took the moral high ground, and only allowed amateurs to compete for them.\", \"from\": 222, \"to\": 304, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Unlike the dirty, rotten commie Soviets.\", \"from\": 305, \"to\": 345, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"They stripped the medals won by Jim Thorpe in the 1912 Olympics from him, when it was discovered that he'd played semi-professional baseball beforehand.\", \"from\": 347, \"to\": 499, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 379, \"end\": 389, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jim_Thorpe\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.413438724426659e-22, \"text\": \"Jim Thorpe\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q14128148\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jim_Thorpe\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jim_Thorpe\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"American leaders got a lot of mileage out of that one; the man who was for a long time considered the greatest athlete who ever lived, lost his medals because we were better than the communists, who trained and sent professional athletes to compete.\", \"from\": 500, \"to\": 749, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 500, \"end\": 508, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.999999881896663, \"rank\": 1.1712885678060396e-07, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Against our wide-eyed, innocent amateurs.\", \"from\": 750, \"to\": 791, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"When USA only won the bronze medal in basketball at the 1988 Olympics, suddenly all that moral fervor was forgotten.\", \"from\": 792, \"to\": 908, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"And so we formed the \\\"Dream Team\\\" of NBA greats, so they would easily win the gold in men's basketball.\", \"from\": 909, \"to\": 1012, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 931, \"end\": 941, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 0.9996406952145133, \"rank\": 0.0003594339316104905, \"text\": \"Dream Team\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\"}, {\"begin\": 946, \"end\": 949, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Basketball_Association\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.776135488817447e-14, \"text\": \"NBA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Basketball_Association\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Basketball_Association\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And they did, proudly hoisting the same medals that poor Jim Thorpe had stolen from him.\", \"from\": 1013, \"to\": 1101, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"For the record, Jim Thorpe never made millions of dollars dunking a ball.\", \"from\": 1102, \"to\": 1175, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1118, \"end\": 1128, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jim_Thorpe\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.413438724426659e-22, \"text\": \"Jim Thorpe\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q14128148\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jim_Thorpe\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jim_Thorpe\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Thorpe, in fact, ravaged by alcoholism, died in poverty.American Memory Hole: ...Jeffries, DonaldCheck Amazon for Pricing.\", \"from\": 1176, \"to\": 1298, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1176, \"end\": 1182, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jeremy_Thorpe\", \"score\": 0.9999992035458024, \"rank\": 7.878325637312073e-07, \"text\": \"Thorpe\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jeremy_Thorpe\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jeremy_Thorpe\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"So I started rooting against America in pretty much every competition after that.\", \"from\": 1300, \"to\": 1381, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"How could you not root for a Serbia or Croatia against a team of entitled and pampered multi-millionaires?\", \"from\": 1382, \"to\": 1488, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1411, \"end\": 1417, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Serbia\", \"score\": 0.9999997203731645, \"rank\": 2.4709371781658265e-07, \"text\": \"Serbia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Serbia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Serbia\"}, {\"begin\": 1421, \"end\": 1428, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Croatia\", \"score\": 0.697325317686938, \"rank\": 0.4340354106820542, \"text\": \"Croatia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Croatia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Croatia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It would be like rooting for that arrogant band of mostly lesbians winning the women's World Cup for America.\", \"from\": 1489, \"to\": 1598, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I do not understand just blindly supporting someone, or some group, just because they come from your country.\", \"from\": 1599, \"to\": 1708, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But then few people have ever called me patriotic, despite my love of the Founding Fathers.\", \"from\": 1709, \"to\": 1800, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I will never get worked up, like Donald Trump did recently, over protesters burning the American flag.\", \"from\": 1801, \"to\": 1903, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1834, \"end\": 1846, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Donald_Trump\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.55419029428306e-19, \"text\": \"Donald Trump\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Donald_Trump\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Donald_Trump\"}, {\"begin\": 1889, \"end\": 1902, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Flag_of_the_United_States\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.352037450095146e-31, \"text\": \"American flag\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Flag_of_the_United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Flag_of_the_United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"What exactly does that flag represent today, to those of us living under the iron \\\"Woke\\\" rule of America 2.0?\", \"from\": 1904, \"to\": 2013, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Everyone has heard by now about the appalling opening ceremonies for the 2024 Olympics in Paris.\", \"from\": 2015, \"to\": 2111, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2105, \"end\": 2110, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.788786293890838e-17, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"There was a blasphemous mockery of the Last Supper, featuring an obese drag queen in the role of Jesus Christ.\", \"from\": 2112, \"to\": 2222, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2177, \"end\": 2182, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Obesity\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.14687035696688e-30, \"text\": \"obese\", \"types\": [\"Q12136\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Obesity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Obesity\"}, {\"begin\": 2209, \"end\": 2221, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\", \"score\": 0.9999999761394068, \"rank\": 2.3860493777250077e-08, \"text\": \"Jesus Christ\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Actually, drag queens played all the parts in this odious spectacle.\", \"from\": 2223, \"to\": 2291, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"No diversity at all.\", \"from\": 2292, \"to\": 2312, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Not a single heterosexual.\", \"from\": 2313, \"to\": 2339, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Now, the \\\"fact checkers\\\" responded to the massive outrage over this by claiming that it was meant to depict an ancient festival honoring the Greek god Dionysus.\", \"from\": 2340, \"to\": 2500, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2481, \"end\": 2486, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greek_mythology\", \"score\": 0.9980794349584863, \"rank\": 0.0015333954681041784, \"text\": \"Greek\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greek_mythology\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greek_mythology\"}, {\"begin\": 2491, \"end\": 2499, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dionysius_of_Halicarnassus\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.5482165106062428e-34, \"text\": \"Dionysus\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dionysius_of_Halicarnassus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dionysius_of_Halicarnassus\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I am sure Dionysus would be honored to know he was portrayed by a drag queen.\", \"from\": 2501, \"to\": 2578, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2511, \"end\": 2519, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dionysius_of_Halicarnassus\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.5482165106062428e-34, \"text\": \"Dionysus\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dionysius_of_Halicarnassus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dionysius_of_Halicarnassus\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Those who can critically think understand perfectly well who and what they were mocking.\", \"from\": 2579, \"to\": 2667, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Jesus Christ is theonlyreligious figure and Christianity is theonlyfaith that can be openly mocked in America 2.0.\", \"from\": 2668, \"to\": 2782, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2668, \"end\": 2680, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\", \"score\": 0.9999999761394068, \"rank\": 2.3860493777250077e-08, \"text\": \"Jesus Christ\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\"}, {\"begin\": 2712, \"end\": 2724, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.9999999999572537, \"rank\": 4.2528294516985684e-11, \"text\": \"Christianity\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"No mockery of Buddha, or Muhammad, or any of the Hindu gods.\", \"from\": 2783, \"to\": 2843, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2797, \"end\": 2803, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gautama_Buddha\", \"score\": 0.999999956972716, \"rank\": 4.299226627951911e-08, \"text\": \"Buddha\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q2566598\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gautama_Buddha\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gautama_Buddha\"}, {\"begin\": 2808, \"end\": 2816, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Muhammad\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.915744894363111e-17, \"text\": \"Muhammad\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Muhammad\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Muhammad\"}, {\"begin\": 2832, \"end\": 2837, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hinduism\", \"score\": 0.9999672284679363, \"rank\": 3.274188981479054e-05, \"text\": \"Hindu\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hinduism\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hinduism\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And it goes without saying that Judaism would never, ever be demeaned in this way.\", \"from\": 2844, \"to\": 2926, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2876, \"end\": 2883, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Judaism\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.8302576833074915e-14, \"text\": \"Judaism\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Judaism\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Judaism\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The opening ceremony, with its theme of utter gayness, brought back memories of the 2012 opening ceremonies in London.\", \"from\": 2928, \"to\": 3046, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3039, \"end\": 3045, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"score\": 0.9999999999599822, \"rank\": 4.032694500089244e-11, \"text\": \"London\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"You know, the one with all those hospital beds.\", \"from\": 3047, \"to\": 3094, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"They trotted out some 300 of these beds, in what we were told was a tribute to the NHS.\", \"from\": 3095, \"to\": 3182, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3178, \"end\": 3181, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Health_Service\", \"score\": 0.9999999999990905, \"rank\": 6.792863267519704e-13, \"text\": \"NHS\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Health_Service\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Health_Service\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I did not realize that hospitals, sickness, or the NHS, had anything whatsoever to do with international sports.\", \"from\": 3183, \"to\": 3295, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3234, \"end\": 3237, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Health_Service\", \"score\": 0.9999999999990905, \"rank\": 6.792863267519704e-13, \"text\": \"NHS\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Health_Service\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Health_Service\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"There were unruly children in the hospital beds, scolded by traditional English nannies.\", \"from\": 3296, \"to\": 3384, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Then a 100 foot figure of what looked like Lord Voldemort but was actually not according to those diligent \\\"fact checkers,\\\" with flaming eyes, accompanied by Captain Hook, Cruella de Vil, and a slew of small black demons, terrified the children.\", \"from\": 3385, \"to\": 3630, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3428, \"end\": 3442, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lord_Voldemort\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Lord Voldemort\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lord_Voldemort\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lord_Voldemort\"}, {\"begin\": 3543, \"end\": 3555, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Captain_Hook\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.6165626560860118e-52, \"text\": \"Captain Hook\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Captain_Hook\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Captain_Hook\"}, {\"begin\": 3557, \"end\": 3571, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cruella_de_Vil\", \"score\": 0.9999999998581188, \"rank\": 1.420608490088177e-10, \"text\": \"Cruella de Vil\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cruella_de_Vil\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cruella_de_Vil\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Finally, the act closed with a giant baby or fetus in the center of the arena.\", \"from\": 3631, \"to\": 3709, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Giant one-eyed pyramids and other occult symbols were featured throughout.\", \"from\": 3710, \"to\": 3784, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Sounds festive.\", \"from\": 3785, \"to\": 3800, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"What child, or parent, would not find allthatentertaining?\", \"from\": 3801, \"to\": 3859, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"So this year's occult-tinged ceremonies were nothing new.\", \"from\": 3861, \"to\": 3918, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It's not like the nations of the world are ever going to get together and use symbols and routines that are religious in nature, celebrating virtue and honoring God.\", \"from\": 3919, \"to\": 4084, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Or at least not defame Him.\", \"from\": 4085, \"to\": 4112, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"For us 'Murricans, there was a lot to be proud of in Paris.\", \"from\": 4113, \"to\": 4172, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4166, \"end\": 4171, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.788786293890838e-17, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Snoop Dogg was chosen to carry the Olympic torch.\", \"from\": 4173, \"to\": 4222, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4173, \"end\": 4183, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Snoop_Dogg\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Snoop Dogg\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Snoop_Dogg\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Snoop_Dogg\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Now, at first glance, this is a strange choice, given his total disconnection from any sport.\", \"from\": 4223, \"to\": 4316, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Unless they have made pot smoking an event now.\", \"from\": 4317, \"to\": 4364, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The venerable Snoop, or in order not to disrespect him, Mr. Dogg, was wearing a Baphomet necklace.\", \"from\": 4365, \"to\": 4463, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The \\\"fact checkers\\\" would probably assure us that Baphomet is actually associated with that Greek god Dionysus or something.\", \"from\": 4464, \"to\": 4588, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4514, 